725581f-a.title: Queens: 69th Street - 63rd Avenue
725581f-a.text:
69th Street, at 63rd Avenue (vantage point), viewing
northeastward from an elevation across Middle Village.
P. L. Sperr  July 7, 1940

725579f-d.title: Queens: 69th Avenue - Queens Boulevard
725579f-d.text:
At the N.E. corner of Sixty-ninth Avenue and Cueens Boulevard,
ahowing the four views of the Ascan Bakus house. In 1923 the Cord
Meyer Development Company was the owner. Oscar William Christian
Backus was born in 1614 and came to this country in 1829. He died March
18, 1880. He married Mary A. Beetham. A daughter,Mary Elisa,married
in 1874 Dr., Howard Lever.
April 1923.
Views 1 and 2.
View 3: March 1925.
View 4: October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
